{"tag":"section","attrib":{"id":"idc9e322fe-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598","identifier":"/us/usc/t43/s455a"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"num","attrib":{"value":"455a"},"text":"§ 455a.","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":" State taxation; lands of desert-land entryman","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"content","attrib":{},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The lands of any desert-land entryman located within an irrigation project constructed under the Reclamation Act and obtaining a water supply from such project, and for whose land water has been actually available for a period of four years, may likewise be taxed by the State or political subdivision thereof in which such lands are located.","children":[],"tail":"\n"}],"tail":null},{"tag":"sourceCredit","attrib":{"id":"idc9e322ff-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"(","children":[{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1928-04-21/ch394/s2"},"text":"Apr. 21, 1928, ch. 394, § 2","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/45/439"},"text":"45 Stat. 439","children":[],"tail":"; "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/act/1930-06-13/ch477"},"text":"June 13, 1930, ch. 477","children":[],"tail":", "},{"tag":"ref","attrib":{"href":"/us/stat/46/581"},"text":"46 Stat. 581","children":[],"tail":".)"}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"notes","attrib":{"type":"uscNote","id":"idc9e32300-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"note","attrib":{"role":"crossHeading","topic":"editorialNotes","id":"idc9e32301-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":null,"children":[{"tag":"b","attrib":{},"text":"Editorial Notes","children":[],"tail":null}],"tail":null}],"tail":"\n"},{"tag":"note","attrib":{"topic":"referencesInText","id":"idc9e32302-3a70-11f1-bde1-a5140e158598"},"text":"\n","children":[{"tag":"heading","attrib":{},"text":"References in Text","children":[],"tail":null},{"tag":"p","attrib":{},"text":"The